# CONSULT-24 — Verdict: read-past mechanism is sound; tri-list garments need one runtime IB scan to close the loop

Your leading hypothesis is **mechanically correct** given the CONSULT-24 gold-standard staging read-back. What remains open is whether garment draws actually have `IB[index] >= m_vertexCount`. Static code analysis says tri-list meshes *should not*, but there is a **confirmed tri-strip remapping bug** in the IB builder and a **D3D11 plugin gap** where the D3D9 vertex-window metadata is silently dropped.

---

## 1. Leading hypothesis: confirm / refute

### CONFIRMED (mechanism)

Given your proven facts:

| Fact | Implication |
|------|-------------|
| `[0, numVerts)` correct and animating at draw | In-range fetches are good |
| `[numVerts, …)` is pure `(0,0,0)` | Any index ≥ `numVerts` reads origin |
| Per-draw `Map(READ)` flush, spikes persist | Not async race; deterministic read-past |
| `lock(m_vertexCount)` writes only that many verts | Tail past slice is never skinned |

Then: **`DrawIndexed` fetches `VB[boundOffset + IB[i] * stride]`. If any `IB[i] ≥ m_vertexCount`, those triangles read the zero tail → collapse to object-space origin → fan to a screen-space spike.**

D3D11 draw path — no vertex-range metadata used:

```3221:3362:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp
void Direct3d11_StateCache::drawPartialIndexedTriangleList(int baseIndex, int minimumVertexIndex, int numberOfVertices, int startIndex, int primitiveCount)
{
	// ...
	Direct3d11_Device::getContext()->DrawIndexed(
		static_cast<UINT>(primitiveCount * 3),
		static_cast<UINT>(startIndex),
		static_cast<INT>(baseIndex));
}
```

Lock writes only `numberOfVertices * vertexSize` bytes; tail of the ring generation stays zero on fresh `WRITE_DISCARD`:

```225:287:src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp
void *Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData::lock(int numberOfVertices, bool forceDiscard)
{
	// ...
	m_numberOfVertices = numberOfVertices;
	m_offset           = ms_used / vertexSize;
	void * const sliceStart = static_cast<char *>(mapped.pData) + ms_used;
	ms_used += length;
	return sliceStart;
}
```

Soft-skin path locks exactly `m_vertexCount`:

```737:776:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp
		m_dynamicStream->lock(m_vertexCount);
		{
			VertexBufferWriteIterator outIt = m_dynamicStream->begin();
			outIt.copy(m_systemStream->beginReadOnly(), m_systemStream->getNumberOfVertices());
		}
		m_dynamicStream->unlock();
```

**If spikes are live while staging shows clean in-range data, the spike almost certainly comes from IB indices that reach into the zero tail — not from VB corruption, bind offset, or races.**

### PARTIALLY REFUTED (automatic for all garments)

For the **standard skeletal tri-list path** (what `SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate` actually builds — `TAG_ITL` / `TAG_OITL` only, no `addTriStripVertex` callers anywhere in `src/`), IB indices are compacted at build time and **should** satisfy `max(IB) ≤ m_vertexCount - 1`:

```1468:1489:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/MeshConstructionHelper.cpp
void MeshConstructionHelper::getTriListTriangle(..., int &index0, int &index1, int &index2) const
{
	// ...
	const size_t vertexDataIndex0 = perShaderData->m_vertexIndices[static_cast<size_t>((*m_indexedTriangles)[indexedTriangleIndex * 3 + 0])];
	index0 = m_vertexData->m_container[vertexDataIndex0].m_shaderVertexIndex;
	// same for index1, index2
}
```

```1194:1194:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp
	m_vertexCount = mesh.getVertexCount(meshPerShaderData);
```

```1234:1237:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/MeshConstructionHelper.cpp
int MeshConstructionHelper::getVertexCount(const PerShaderData *perShaderData) const
{
	return perShaderData->m_usedVertexCount;
}
```

`prepareForReading()` assigns `m_shaderVertexIndex` sequentially `0 … m_usedVertexCount-1` only to `m_isUsed` vertices; triangle verts are marked used in `addTriListTri`. So for tri lists, **`maxVbIndex` tracked at `:1528-1529` should equal `m_vertexCount - 1`**.

**You have not yet proven runtime IB violation** — your staging probe scans the VB linearly and uses the RenderCommand *window* (`minVtx + numVtx - 1`), not the actual max value stored in the static IB. You need one more probe: at garment draw, scan `m_indexBuffer[startIndex … startIndex + primCount*3)` for `max(IB[i])` and compare to `m_vertexCount` / `runStart`.

